This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The paper proposes a novel tracking algorithm that combines circular correlation filters and structural operators. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses computational efficiency, which could potentially place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Robotics (cs.RO) categories.
